title: War-audiophile Gold disks; ll Day Music and Deliver the Word EAC
description:
Here are two fantastic albums from the early 70's LA afro-funk band War. Each has been remastered in 1995 from the 20 bit from the original master tapes, overseen by the original producers. The sound quality is superb. 

Deliver the Word includes extended funk groove jams 'Me and Baby Brother', 'Gypsy Man' and 'Southern Part of Texas', with all the remaining tracks being equally as strong. 

All Day Music also has 'Slippin in to Darkness', 'Nappy Head' as well as a live jam of 'Baby Brother'. 

These albums were from the halycon days when there was no dead space on the LPs...each and every track is a winner.
